# Host-based rewrite: the In-DROP calculator shares this Netlify project/deploy
# with the main retirement calculator (in-drop.html is a second Vite entry
# point, built alongside index.html). Requests to this subdomain's root get
# index.html swapped for in-drop.html; every other host is untouched.
#
# Deliberately NOT a /* wildcard: this app has no client-side router, so the
# only path that ever needs rewriting is the bare "/". A wildcard here also
# rewrites /assets/*.js requests to in-drop.html's markup (wrong content-type,
# app fails to mount with no visible console error) — confirmed by testing.
# Static files (JS/CSS/favicon/icons) resolve normally on every host as-is.
#
# The trailing "!" (force) is required: without it, Netlify skips a redirect
# rule whenever the requested path already resolves to a real file, and since
# domain aliases share the same file system as the primary domain, "/" always
# resolves to index.html by default. Confirmed by testing — the unforced rule
# silently lost to that default and kept serving index.html on this subdomain.
https://indrop.shifttowealthplanning.com/  /in-drop.html  200!
